init_text:
Are We Being Bad Citizens If We Don't Keep Up With the News?

In your opinion, are we being bad citizens if we don't keep up with the news? Do you think all people have some responsibility to know what is going on in the world? Does engaging with current events actually do anything at all? Why do you think the way you do?

---

In my opinion,

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Just paying attention to what's going on in our environment will do just fine.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: whole idea of "news" has become more and more warped.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Paying attention and being connected to our communities alone will do a lot to keep our citizens informed.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I'd say people shouldn't be worried about not keeping up with the news.
